Package: pathos
Title: Flip Between Paths and Edges
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Michael D.","Sumner", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "mdsumner@gmail.com"))
Description: A 'path' is one way to think about a sequence of ordered records and another is as a 'set of edges', 
    links to the previous record is another. This package provides tools to easily convert between these two models. 
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: raster, 
         dplyr, 
         tibble
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat
ByteCompile: true

